## Hardware & Runtime Context

- **CPU/Memory:** Apple M5 Pro Silicon / 24GB Unified Memory
- **Package Manager:** pnpm (content-addressable storage)
- **Terminal:** Warp (block-compatible non-interactive outputs)
- **Virtualization:** OrbStack (native Docker replacement)
- **Local Inference:** Ollama serving Qwen 3.6 Coder 14B/32B

## AI Model Routing (Soft Preference)

> **Prefer local Ollama (Qwen 3.6 Coder 14B) for routine tasks** — file edits, simple refactors, lookups, and code formatting — to preserve the 24GB RAM headroom.
>
> **Use cloud Claude** for:
> - Complex architectural decisions
> - Multi-file refactors spanning 3+ modules
> - Domain modeling and PRD synthesis
> - When local model is unavailable or hits its context window
>
> When in doubt, start with the local model. Escalate to cloud only when needed.

